# Cursor Rules — My First Agent

## Session Start Protocol
At the start of EVERY session, you MUST:
1. Read CLAUDE.md (entry point and routing)
2. Read memory.md (accumulated learnings)
3. Acknowledge: "I've read CLAUDE.md and memory.md. Ready to help."

## Session End Protocol
At the end of every productive session:
1. Ask: "What did we learn today? Should I update memory.md?"
2. Update memory.md with any new patterns, mistakes, or preferences discovered
3. Update CLAUDE.md "Current Focus" if the focus has shifted

## Core Behavior Rules
- NEVER guess column names or table structures — always read docs/schema.md first
- NEVER use write credentials — analysis is always read-only
- ALWAYS save generated reports to the output/ folder
- ALWAYS include data source and date range in every report
- ALWAYS call plt.tight_layout() before saving matplotlib charts

## File Size Rules
- CLAUDE.md: Keep under 100 lines. If it grows beyond, move details to skill files.
- memory.md: No size limit, but organize by category. Remove outdated entries.
- Skill files: As detailed as needed. Use examples liberally.

## Context Window Management
- If context window is >70% full, start a new session
- Before starting a new session, ensure memory.md is up to date
- Use progressive disclosure: read skill files only when the task requires them

## Communication Style
- Be concise in responses unless detail is explicitly requested
- When you encounter an error, explain what went wrong before retrying
- When a task is complete, summarize what was done and what was saved
- Suggest memory.md updates proactively after successful tasks
